description: {"blocks":[{"key":"671ol","text":"Indoor air pollution in office buildings is complex and serious. This research is targeted at three types of air pollutants: CO2, VOCs, and PM2.5. In order to seek the optimal control method to achieve good indoor air quality, an orthogonal experiment was carried out in the environmental chamber to compare the control time and energy consumption of four control methods (purifier+ and window+, purifier+ and window-, purified fresh air 240 m3/h and purified fresh air 400 m3/h) required for pollutants to meet the standard. The result shows that the purifier+ and window+ method is more effective in most conditions. Its control time is reduced by 8.06% and the energy consumption is reduced by 11.91% compared with the traditional control method of purified fresh air 240 m3/h. This research guides the optimization control strategy of indoor air quality under different pollution conditions in office buildings.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":127,"length":1},{"style":"sub","offset":142,"length":3},{"style":"sup","offset":443,"length":1},{"style":"sup","offset":475,"length":1},{"style":"sup","offset":776,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
guidelines: {"blocks":[{"key":"1r8ur","text":"This experiment aims to obtain the optimal coordinated control method under different multiple pollutants conditions; provide guidance for building designers, building occupants, and building managers on the comprehensive management of indoor multi-pollutants for excellent indoor air quality.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"e2f5e","text":"Turn on the air conditioning. Turn on all the temperature, humidity, and indoor air quality sensors. Close the doors and windows. Start the experiment.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"eqs6o","text":"Create the indoor air pollution sources artificially until the CO2, VOCs, and PM2.5 in the breathing zone have exceeded the values set for each condition, and then stabilize for 2 minutes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":65,"length":1},{"style":"sub","offset":80,"length":3}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"264qf","text":"Turn on the air purifier or purified fresh air system according to the condition, and set the fresh air volume. Turn on the time monitor and energy power monitor to record the control time and energy consumption.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cprbf","text":"When all the IAQ sensors show that CO2, VOCs, and PM2.5 are below the standard, record the time and energy power again. Then stabilize for 5 minutes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":37,"length":1},{"style":"sub","offset":52,"length":3}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"6dt84","text":"Turn off all the equipment and sensors and end the experiment.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
